### 1) List all contacts
GET http://localhost:8080/api/contacts
Accept: application/json

### 2) Create a contact with a FIXED _id (requires the POST tweak above)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/contacts
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "_id": "64a64a64a64a64a64a64a64a",
  "firstName": "Fixed",
  "lastName": "Person",
  "email": "fixed.person@example.test",
  "favoriteColor": "teal",
  "birthday": "2001-01-01"
}

### 3) Get that one contact
GET http://localhost:8080/api/contacts/64a64a64a64a64a64a64a64a
Accept: application/json

### 4) Update that contact (expects 204 No Content)
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/contacts/64a64a64a64a64a64a64a64a
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "firstName": "FixedUpdated",
  "lastName": "Person",
  "email": "fixed.person@example.test",
  "favoriteColor": "blue",
  "birthday": "2001-01-02"
}

### 5) Delete that contact (expects 204 No Content)
DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/contacts/64a64a64a64a64a64a64a64a
Accept: application/json

### 6) Verify deletion (should be 404)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/contacts/64a64a64a64a64a64a64a64a
Accept: application/json